            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Please do not send your child to this school if their mental health matters to you.\n\nAt first glance, Vidyodaya School seems like a paradise – lush greenery, well-dressed students, and an air of exclusivity. But if your child's mental well-being matters, I strongly advise against sending them here.\n\nAs a former student, I can say with confidence that behind the polished image lies a deeply flawed system. Teachers wield unnecessary power, fabricating stories about students and creating unnecessary trouble for both them and their parents. The school fosters an environment of stress and anxiety rather than learning and growth.\n\nEverything revolves around money. While donations for relief funds are understandable, forcing students—including those who have personally suffered in the disaster—to contribute is beyond insensitive. And despite all the money they collect, the infrastructure remains shockingly inadequate. Some blocks don’t even have proper washrooms, especially for girls, which is unacceptable in any educational institution.\n\nNormal friendships between boys and girls are scrutinized, and having a relationship is treated like a crime. The school creates unnecessary fear and stress instead of fostering a healthy environment.\n\nA school should nurture and protect its students, not exploit them. If you want a place where your child will genuinely thrive, look elsewhere.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
