          },
          "datePublished": "2024-08-12",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "2",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Vidyodaya School is a truly remarkable institution with an aesthetically pleasing campus and a commendable education system. The teachers are dedicated and genuinely committed to fostering a supportive learning environment. However, there is a significant concern that requires immediate attention.\n\nThe requirement for students to attend school on nearly every Saturday is a considerable burden for families. Weekends are the only opportunity we have for meaningful family interactions and relaxation. This schedule severely restricts our ability to connect as a family unit. This concern has been raised repeatedly during parent-teacher meetings, and it is clear that many other parents share this frustration.\n\nWhile it may be true that other schools follow similar practices, Vidyodaya, as one of the leading schools in Ernakulam, has the unique opportunity to set a progressive standard. A school of this caliber should recognize the importance of balancing academic excellence with respecting family time. Education extends beyond academics; it is also about nurturing well-rounded individuals with strong family ties.\n\nIt is imperative that Vidyodaya reevaluates this policy and considers the well-being of both students and their families. By addressing this issue, the school can enhance its reputation and demonstrate leadership in fostering a more holistic approach to education.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
